  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TSSA New Berth</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project is to refurbish and expand Tecon Salvador S.A.s (TSSA) container terminal inside the Port of Salvador, which is located in the state of Bahia in North East Brazil. The Project includes (i) the refurbishment of 2 berths with a combined total length of 617 meters; (ii) the installation of three Post-Panamax Ship-to-Shore cranes and six Rubber Tyred Gantries Cranes; (iii) the refurbishment of existing buildings and expansion of the container yard from 58.7 hectares to 95.2 hectares; and (iv) the development of supporting electrical infrastructure. Upon completion, the terminals container handling capacity will increase from 250,000 twenty foot equivalent container units (TEUs) to 500,000 TEUs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project will help strengthen the port sector in Brazil by increasing container handling capacity at the Port of Salvador, which is critical to enabling further trade growth for Northeast Brazil and to strengthening Bahia&apos;s position as an investment destination. The Project will also create direct and indirect employment opportunities and increase revenues for the Government of Brazil through increased economic activity and higher tax payments, custom duties, and lease payments.</narrative>
  </description>
